description:
amount of electric conducting routes of an object carrying the current, contributing to thermal losses in type and  routine tests.
1 Under type and routine tests all current paths are considered to contribute to the power loss of the considered object.

2 Several current pathes may occurr in different product types, e.g. 3-phase transformer, a power relay, contactor which may be only partially used in operation. Less current paths used in operation reduce power loss.
